/*****************************************************************
 * File:    Intrprtr.doc
 * Purpose: Describe the interpreter
 * Author:  Karl Abrahamson
 ****************************************************************/


          =====================================
	  High level description of interpreter
          =====================================

  REMARKS
  Terminology is somewhat strange, since provisional terms were used
  and then modified.  The word 'type' is sometimes used in place of 
  species, sometimes in place of genus, when the genus is given by a
  type expression.   The word 'class' is used in some places to mean genus,
  community, species or family.  The word 'entity' is used for a data item.
  In some places, the word 'place' is used for shared box, 
  and 'box' for nonshared box.


     ======================================================
			Overview
     ======================================================

The main program is in file src/intrprtr/intrprtr.c.  It reads
command line options, initializes, and calls the package reader to
read in the packages.  It then calls the evaluator on each execute
declaration encountered.

The package reader is in src/intrprtr/package.c.  It reads the packages
and sets up data structures that describe the packages.  

The evaluator is in src/evaluate/evaluate.c.  It processes instructions,
one after another.  The instructions are for an abstract machine whose
basic objects are described in src/machdata/entity.h, and further in
src/machdata/sment.h or src/machdata/lgent.h.  Data structures for
the abstract machine are described in src/machstrc.  The language of the
abstract machine is described in src/evaluate/language.doc.

