  m_tyutil.c:  More utilities for the interpreter.


src/machstrc/*
--------------------
  Abstract machine data structures.

  The currently running function is described by variable the_act.
  Variable the_act has type ACTIVATION.  In general, type ACTIVATION is
  used to describe a running thread.

  The_act.continuations is a linked chain of frames describing the 
  run-time stack of functions waiting for called functions to return.
  The nodes of that chain have type CONTINUATION.  (A continuation holds
  a subset of the information held in an activation.)

  The_act.stack is a stack that is used for instruction execution.  
  For example, the addition function pops two numbers from the stack 
  and pushes their sum.  The return value of a function is placed 
  on the stack. Continuations do not store a stack, since one stack is
  shared.  The stack structure is described by type STACK.

  The_act.env points to an environment structure that describes identifier
  bindings.  The environment has type ENVIRONMENT.

  The_act.contol is a list of branch-points and try-points, indicating
  what the current thread should do when it fails.  It is a chain of
  nodes of type CONTROL.

  The_act.coroutines is a list of activations of sibling coroutines.

  machStrc.h:		Prototypes
  actvn.c:		Activations and continuations.
  actvn.doc:		Discussion of activations and continuations.
  control.c:		The control, used for backtracking, etc.
  environ.c:		The environment (for identifier bindings).
  envsize.c:		Sizes for environment frames.
  stack.c:		The stack, used for computation of expressions.
  state.c:		The state (box bindings).
  

